2005-06-02  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* configure.ac: Fixed a wrong error message.
	* app/CharacterWindow.h, app/CharacterWindow.cpp: Added a function to
	  respond to <return> keys in the combo box. If <return> is pressed we
	  won't allow the normal signal handler to act and pop the list but
	  will activate the dialog's default action.

2005-06-02  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* configure.ac: Relax mercator version requirement.

2005-06-01  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.h, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp: Fixed
	  an error with counting the overall count of types to upload. Changed
	  the text of progress bars to "x of y" instead of "x / y". Added more
	  commentaries (so I understand it myself :)).
	* gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.cpp: Correctly act when the dialog was closed with
	  the "X" button.

2005-06-01  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.h, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp: The
	  types are now displayed in a tree list view. The way it is done
	  automatically takes care of dependency problems and better visualizes
	  the structure of the types tree.
	* TODO: Please investigate leaks in the ImportTypesWizard.

2005-05-21  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.h, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp: Added
	  the necessary logic and stuff to not only import new types but also
	  update existing ones. This is done using Eris' TypeService
	  infrasturcture. Thanks for the fix, James.

2005-05-20  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.h, gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.cpp: Moved the creation and
	  updating of types from the TypeTree to the ImportTypesWizard. This
	  the UI is better to handle and the process of adding types is done
	  when the wizard is closed. No dialogs popping out of nowhere when an
	  error occures.
	* gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.h, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp: As
	  there is no need to access the types from outside the wizard I
	  removed the iterators. Added another page to the wizard that monitors
	  the upload status of the selected types.

2005-05-20  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.cpp: Added an error message dialog when the user
	  is not logged in yet. This prevents a segfault.

2005-05-20  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.h, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp:
	  Added an iterator class so we can iterate through the types that were
	  selected to be imported.

	* gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.h, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp: Going through
	  the list of selected classes and doing Create ops for each of them.
	  A responder connected on Eris level is responsible for getting error
	  messages displayed to the user.

	* AUTHORS: Added me.

2005-05-18  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.cpp, gui/gtkmm/ImportTypesWizard.h:
	  This is a two-step dialog box that lets you choose a file, reads the
	  content and in the second step displays the types from the file
	  letting you pick some/all to be imported on the server.

	* gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.cpp, gui/gtkmm/TypeTree.h: UI (toolbar) is handled
	  by UIManager. Added a pointer to an ImportTypesWizard so we can have
	  _one_ wizard per TypeTree.

2005-05-16  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* configure.ac: Require the correct version of eris.

2005-05-01  Hagen Möbius  <hagen.moebius@starschiffchen.de>

	* app/ServerWindow.h, app/ServerWindow.cpp: Added actions, buttons and
	  handlers for displaying chat window.

	* Added gui/gtkmm/ChatWindow.h, gui/gtkmm/ChatWindow.cpp,
	  gui/gtkmm/PanelNotebook.h, gui/gtkmm/PanelNotebook.cpp: In essence a
	  copy from silence. All classes packed into one file because they are
	  really closely realated. The ChatWindow initializes the lobby chat
	  and all private chats. The classes in PanelNotebook provide a
	  notebook with tabs that color on content change. The room tabs have
	  a treeview aside that displays the names of users inside the same
	  room. Additionally they have a dialog button that let's you start a
	  private conversation with the selected person. There are still some
	  things to do but this is a functional version to look at.

