	* app/ServerEntities.cpp, app/Server.h, app/Server.cpp:
	  Set loc on move operations, so it works for privileged avatars.

2002-02-08  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/ServerEntities.h, app/ServerEntities.cpp:
	  Implemented dragging to move entities.

	* app/Server.h, app/Server.cpp: Added method to move entites
	  around using priveleged avatar.

	* app/MainWindow.h, app/MainWindow.cpp, app/GlView.cpp,
	  app/GlView.cpp: Experiment with Gtkmm idle features.
	  Add more edit menu entries, with accelerators.

Thursday, February 07 2002, James Turner <james@worldforge.org>

	* ServerEntities.cpp/.h: Bind to various Eris signals, notably
	  EntiyCreate and Changed, to trigger a model update (and
	  hence a redraw) when server-driven changes occur. This
	  means movement and so on should be visible now.
	* Modified configure.in to check for ris and skstream using
	  the appropriate macros (AM_PATH_ERIS / AM_PATH_SKSTREAM)

2002-01-30  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/GlView.cpp: Modify the projection so there is not so much
	  wasted depth buffer.

	* app/Model.cpp: Fix popping selection.

	* app/NewServerWindow.cpp, app/NewServerWindow.h, app/Server.cpp,
	  app/Server.h: Initialise all pointers to ensure they are not
	  being used un-initialised. Set the deafult host to localhost.
	  Switch to using term "Avatar" instead of "Agent".

	* app/ServerEntities.cpp, app/ServerEntities.h: Modify how selection
	  is stored into a primary selection, selection list, and stack
	  of pushed primary selections. Implement selecting single entity
	  correctly, and pushing it onto the stack. Use stack to view
	  container contents.

2002-01-29  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/BladeMap.cpp, app/Palette.cpp, app/ServerEntities.cpp,
	  app/Vector3D.h, app/Vector3D.cpp, app/ViewWindow.cpp:
	  gcc v3 fixes contributed by Malcolm Walker.

	* app/GlView.cpp: Implemented blender style view control using
	  numeric keypad.

	* app/NewServerWindow.cpp: Switch to using hostname entry for server,
	  though this still causes segfaults occasionally.

2002-01-25  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/BladeMap.h, app/EntityLayer.h, app/GlView.cpp,
	  app/Holo.h, app/IsoMap.h, app/Layer.h, app/ServerEntities.h:
	  Added insert method, which inserts a new object into the layer
	  at the given position.

	* app/Palette.cpp, app/Palette.h: Added code to store, set and
	  retreive current selection.

	* app/Server.h, app/Server.cpp: Added method to create new
	  entity in game world, using current character. Made callbacks
	  used only within this class private, so it is clear they
	  should not be called from elsewhere.

	* app/ServerEntities.cpp: Implemented inserting an object of type
	  selected in the palette, at the postion of the cursor.

2002-01-20  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/GlView.cpp, app/GlView.h: Added new view submenu to control
	  direction world is viewed from. Now it is possible to view
	  the world from any angle. Added a cursor, which can be
	  moved around using the draw tool. Implemented update of
	  display when clicks have been processed.

	* app/Model.cpp, Model.h, app/NewServerWindow.cpp:
	  Store pointer the the Server object associated with this model.

	* app/Palette.cpp: Ensure that the palette knows about a model
	  early enough.

	* app/ServerEntities.cpp, app/ServerEntities.h: Register game_entity
	  types with the palette as the type nodes are bound by Eris.

	* app/ViewWindow.cpp, app/ViewWindow.h: Add a status bar that
	  displays the cursor world coords.

	* app/Palette.h, app/Palette.cpp, app/IsoMap.cpp, app/BladeMap.cpp,
	  app/ServerEntities.cpp: Added signal used to indicate to
	  the palette that 1 or more new types have been installed. Intended
	  to be more efficient than updating everytime a new one is added.

2002-01-18  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/Palette.h, app/Palette.cpp: Implemented storing lists
	  of items of the diferent types, registration of these types
	  by layers, and display of these lists according to the
	  model being worked on.

	* app/Model.h, app/Model.cpp: Add reference to main window, to
	  allow model code to register things with other windows.

	* app/IsoMap.h, app/IsoMap.cpp, app/BladeMap.h, app/BladeMap.cpp:
	  Register tile and texture types with the palette.

2002-01-16  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/GlView.cpp: Added face() method which reorients the modelview
	  so that things can be drawn with constant rotation with respect
	  to the camera. Precent origin() from calling make_current(), as
	  it is always called from within drawing code.

	* app/GlView.cpp, app/LayerWindow.cpp, app/MainWindow.cpp,
	  app/MainWindow.h, app/Model.h, 
	  Added a signal which indicates that the users current model has
	  changed. Removed arguments and features elsewhere in the code which
	  used other techniques to track the same information.

	* app/InheritanceWindow.cpp, app/LayerWindow.cpp, app/MainWindow.cpp,
	  app/MainWindow.h, app/NewServerWindow.cpp, app/ServerWindow.cpp,
	  app/equator_plugin.cpp:
	  Switched all top level windows to being stored as references
	  so that they can be made public without fear of tampering.
	  No longer necessary to pass reference to Gtk::Main to the
	  MainWindow constructor.

	* app/Palette.cpp, app/Palette.h:
	  Implemented notebook palette interface.

2002-01-16  Al Riddoch  <alriddoch@zepler.org>

	* app/Model.h, app/Model.cpp: Add update method, so other code can
	  notify that the models data has changed, and cause Model to emit
	  a signal.

	* app/Palette.h, app/Palette.cpp, app/MainWIndow.h, app/MainWindow.cpp:
	  Beginnings of dialogue which will allow tiles, entities, textures
	  etc to be selected for adding to models.

	* app/Layer.h: Add method which toggles layers visibility.

	* app/LayerWindow.h, app/LayerWindow.cpp: Use pixmap of eye
	  to indicate if a layer is visible, and implement toggling of
	  layers visibility by clicking on the column in the layers window.

	* app/GlView.cpp: Only render layer if it is supposed to be visible.

